WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.800
Hello, my name is Hannah Frick.

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:08.800
My name is Emil Wietveld.

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:13.000
And my name is Simon, and we'd like to share with you our top three reasons why we think

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.879
you should attend our workshop at PositConf this year.

00:00:16.879 --> 00:00:21.240
Tidymodels is a framework for modeling using tidyverse principles.

00:00:21.240 --> 00:00:26.879
So it's built to make your modeling practice ergonomic, effective, and safe.

00:00:26.879 --> 00:00:33.279
By ergonomic, we mean that if you're a tidyverse user, tidymodels code will feel expressive

00:00:33.279 --> 00:00:35.439
and fluent to you.

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:40.000
As for effectiveness, tidymodels equips you to build performant models quickly, and once

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.320
you've got the basics, puts highly advanced tools at your fingertips.

00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:49.360
Lastly, tidymodels is safe, in that we build the packages to protect you against common

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:56.599
failures models typically adapt, such as overfitting and data retention.

00:00:56.599 --> 00:01:01.520
Tidymodels is stable and production ready, so now is a good time to learn it.

00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.799
Secondly, the instructors.

00:01:03.799 --> 00:01:10.519
Hannah, Simon, and I are programmers, and we work on the tidymodels packages full time.

00:01:10.519 --> 00:01:15.360
But we're also educators, and we teach tidymodels regularly.

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:20.680
So that means the material, and the code in there, has been through several cohorts of

00:01:20.680 --> 00:01:23.199
workshop attendees and their feedback.

00:01:23.199 --> 00:01:29.120
So when we say tidymodels is stable, we also mean the interface and the way we teach it

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:31.040
is tried and tested.

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:33.699
The third reason is the level of the workshop.

00:01:33.699 --> 00:01:39.519
This year, we are offering both an introductory tidymodels workshop, this one, and an advanced

00:01:39.519 --> 00:01:41.459
one taught by Max Kuhn.

00:01:41.459 --> 00:01:44.440
So that means this one will be a true beginner's workshop.

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:49.239
If you already use tidymodels, take the advanced one.

00:01:49.239 --> 00:01:55.239
Or if you want to learn all these tidymodels, take this one, and take the advanced one the next day.

00:01:55.239 --> 00:02:00.239
So if you'd like to join us in Chicago, please go to posit.co.com, and we hope to see you there.

